\name{par2ppfd}
\alias{par2ppfd}
\title{par2ppfd}
\usage{
par2ppfd(watts)
}
\arguments{
  \item{PAR}{(W / m2)}
}
\value{
PPFD (mol / m2 / s)
}
\description{
convert PAR to PPFD
}
\details{
Converts photosynthetically active radiation (PAR, units of
Watts / m2) to photosynthetic photon flux density (PPFD) in
units of mol / m2 / s From Campbell and Norman p151 PPFD =
PAR * (J/m2/s) * (1 mol / 2.35e5 J) 2.35e5 J / mol is the
energy content of solar radiation in the PAR waveband 0.486
is based on the approximation that PAR is 0.45-0.50 of the
total radiation
}
